divs: Sighting DetailsI was driving from camp Pendleton outside of the basilone gate wgen I noticed a large, glowing, cylindrical object flying at about 50 knots and at a steep nosedive land into the water. It made barely any splash and no sound that I could hear. The object left a greenish luminescent trail behind it as it landed and glew for a few seconds in the water. I tried to see if it was just maybe a green light reflecting off of my windshield and maybe I was just seeing thi ngs but I could not recreate the sighting. I am not the only person to see the onject but others wish not to come forth
trends: There have been no other sightings in Camp Pendleton North
This sighting has never been favorited.
Summary: a green glowing cigar shaped object nose dived into the pacific ocean
